#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:27
msgid "Optional Physics Package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:29
msgid ""
"The regular `miniworlds` package contains the core 2D engine. Physics "
"support is provided by a separate package so that the base installation "
"stays small and works reliably in school environments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:33
msgid ""
"Install physics support only when you need gravity, bouncing, joints, or "
"collision simulation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:40
msgid "Then import the physics world from the separate package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:47
msgid ""
"See [World > PhysicsWorld](../api/world_physics.md) for the API and a "
"first example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:50
msgid "Python And Runtime Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:52
msgid ""
"Miniworlds runs with Python and pygame-ce. Use a current Python 3 "
"installation when possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:55
msgid ""
"Some learning environments run Python in the browser, for example Pyodide"
" or H5P-based tasks. These environments are useful for tutorials and "
"small examples, but they may not support every desktop feature. In "
"particular, physics support depends on the separate `miniworlds_physics` "
"package and may be limited or unavailable in browser runtimes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:61
#, fuzzy
msgid "With Thonny"
msgstr "With Thonny"

#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:63
msgid ""
"First click on **\"Tools → Manage Packages\"**. Then enter "
"`\"miniworlds\"` in the search field and install **miniworlds**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/01_installation.md:65
msgid ""
"If you want to use physics examples in Thonny, also install "
"`miniworlds_physics` in the same package manager."
msgstr ""

